# Survey wording (no "wizard")

Do **not** use the word **wizard** anywhere in this project—in UI copy, comments, README, commit messages, or when describing the multi-step survey.

Use instead: **survey steps**, **step-by-step flow**, **multi-step form**, or **sections**.

This matches the project owner’s preference; keep language respectful and plain.
